						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">clueless wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">(Someone once mentioned that the required number of gates in a PLC for MMC3 exceeded what was cost-effective or something).</div>
<br />Which is why someone else recommended making a reduced MMC3 with less support for CHR bankswitching (e.g. don't implement CHR bank registers 0-4) so that it could fit in commonly available 5.0 V CPLDs. That led to <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=51785#51785" class="postlink">this</a> and <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=65606#65606" class="postlink">this</a>.</div>

